title.rendered: In IPL 2023 Qualifier 1, GT vs CSK: Head-to-head, key battles, key players

content.rendered:
IPL 2023: Before the match between the two teams kicks off, let’s look at the battles between the two sides, the players to look out for, and many more –

The MS Dhoni-led Chennai Super Kings are set to face Gujarat Titans in Qualifier 1 of IPL 2023 at the MA Chidambaram Stadium in Chennai on Tuesday. CSK are four-time title winners, winning in 2010, 2011, 2018, and 2021. On the other hand, Hardik Pandya and Co. are the defending champions. GT was one of the two IPL teams in 2022. CSK and GT are known for their consistency and match-winners. In IPL 2023, GT finished at the top of the table with 20 points while CSK ended up at the second spot with 17 points to their credit.

Before the match between the two teams kicks off, let’s look at the battles between the two sides –

Head-to-head record:

It is interesting to note that CSK is yet to win over GT. Both sides played three matches and Gujarat won them all. The matches took place in Pune, Mumbai and Ahmedabad. In the ongoing season, GT defeated CSK by 5 wickets while chasing a 179-run target.

Key Battles:

MS Dhoni vs Hardik Pandya

The healthy fight between MS Dhoni and Hardik Pandya’s strategies will be ahead of anything between MS Dhoni and Hardik Pandya’s strategies. One is a world-class leader, while the other is an emerging one with a promising future. Who outsmarts whom will be interesting to watch!

CSK openers vs Mohammed Shami

CSK openers — Ruturaj Gaikwad and Devon Conway — are the top scorers for the side. While Gaikwad has scored over 500 runs, Conway has scored close to 600. However, both batters have a real threat in GT’s star pacer Mohammed Shami. The right-arm speedster has dominated Gaikwad in the past, while he has been excellent with the ball against Conway this season.

Deepak Chahar vs Shubman Gill

CSK pacer Deepak Chahar is finally back in his groove, picking up 10 wickets in the last four matches. His swing at the start makes him almost unplayable during the powerplay. GT’s in-form opener Shubman Gill could face a tough challenge from the star pacer with veteran MS Dhoni guiding his bowler from behind the stumps.

Players to watch out for:

Shubman Gill – He enters Qualifiers 1 riding back-to-back centuries. He is hot with 680 runs and a 152.47 strike rate.

Devon Conway – He is CSK’s top-scorer in the ongoing season. His strike rate (138.63) has also been impressive.

Mohammed Shami – The right-arm pacer is GT’s joint-highest wicket-taker with 24 wickets to his name. Meanwhile, he has an impressive 7.70 average for the season.

Rashid Khan – The spin wizard continues to charm. When his bowling failed to impress anyone, he must have done it with his batting skills. The Afghan leggie also has 24 wickets to his credit.

Listen to the latest songs only on JioSaavn.com

MS Dhoni – The legendary captain is always the focus on the field. The ongoing season has been successful for Dhoni as he contributed to CSK’s strong finishes. Meanwhile, his tactics as captain is one of the big factors for CSK’s success over the years.

When will the match start: 7 pm (toss), Game starts at 7:30 pm
